HEADWORD: Charade
<hw>Cha*rade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>charade</ets>, cf. Pr. <ets>charrada</ets> long chat, It
<ets>ciarlare</ets> to chat, whence E. <ets>charlatan</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A verbal or acted enigma based upon a word which has two or more
significant syllables or parts, each of which, as well as the word
itself, is to be guessed from the descriptions or
representations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Charadriidae</ent>⟦br⟧
